Oppenheimer & Co. Inc. Reduces Stake in Alcoa Corp. (AA)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

Oppenheimer & Co. Inc. cut its position in Alcoa Corp. (NYSE:AA) by 38.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 9,080 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 5,605 shares during the period. Oppenheimer & Co. Inc.’s holdings in Alcoa Corp. were worth $313,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
A number of other institutional investors have also modified their holdings of AA. Private Advisor Group LLC raised its position in Alcoa Corp. by 16.3% in the first quarter. Private Advisor Group LLC now owns 9,225 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $312,000 after buying an additional 1,294 shares in the last quarter. Nordea Investment Management AB raised its position in Alcoa Corp. by 21.2% in the first quarter. Nordea Investment Management AB now owns 25,648 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $882,000 after buying an additional 4,494 shares in the last quarter. Pacer Advisors Inc. raised its position in Alcoa Corp. by 3.3% in the first quarter. Pacer Advisors Inc. now owns 4,140 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $142,000 after buying an additional 132 shares in the last quarter. Penserra Capital Management LLC purchased a new position in Alcoa Corp. during the first quarter valued at about $1,262,000. Finally, Oxford Asset Management purchased a new position in Alcoa Corp. during the first quarter valued at about $499,000. 


 Get Alcoa Corp. alerts:



Shares of Alcoa Corp. (NYSE:AA) traded down 0.27% on Friday, hitting $36.62. 2,527,539 shares of the company’s stock were exchanged. Alcoa Corp. has a 12-month low of $20.00 and a 12-month high of $39.78. The stock has a market cap of $6.75 billion and a price-to-earnings ratio of 196.88. The company’s 50-day moving average price is $33.13 and its 200 day moving average price is $33.85. 




Alcoa Corp. (NYSE:AA) last issued its earnings results on Wednesday, July 19th. The industrial products company reported $0.62 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.60 by $0.02. The business had revenue of $2.86 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $2.88 billion. Alcoa Corp. had a net margin of 1.63% and a return on equity of 3.28%. The business’s quarterly revenue was up 23.1% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the previous year, the firm earned $0.15 earnings per share. On average, equities analysts predict that Alcoa Corp. will post $2.83 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY NOTICE: This report was originally posted by BNB Daily and is owned by of BNB Daily. If you are viewing this report on another site, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of United States and international copyright and trademark laws. The original version of this report can be viewed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/23/oppenheimer-co-inc-decreases-stake-in-alcoa-corp-aa-updated-updated.html. 
Several equities analysts have issued reports on AA shares. Berenberg Bank raised shares of Alcoa Corp. from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and lifted their price target for the stock from $27.00 to $40.00 in a report on Friday, March 24th. BMO Capital Markets raised shares of Alcoa Corp. from a “market perform” rating to an “outperform” rating and boosted their price objective for the company from $35.00 to $45.00 in a report on Friday, March 31st. Zacks Investment Research lowered shares of Alcoa Corp. from a “strong-buy” rating to a “hold” rating in a report on Monday, April 3rd. Cowen and Company boosted their price objective on shares of Alcoa Corp. from $29.00 to $35.00 and gave the company an “outperform” rating in a report on Wednesday, April 19th. Finally, Citigroup Inc. reissued a “buy” rating and set a $45.00 price objective on shares of Alcoa Corp. in a report on Friday, May 19th. Five analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating, fifteen have assigned a buy rating and one has assigned a strong buy rating to the stock. Alcoa Corp. currently has a consensus rating of “Buy” and a consensus target price of $38.83.
Alcoa Corp. Company Profile
Alcoa Corporation, formerly Alcoa Upstream Corporation, is engaged in the production of bauxite, alumina and aluminum of various cast and rolled products. The Company is engaged in the production and management of aluminum and alumina combined through its participation in various aspects of the industry, such as technology, mining, refining, smelting, and recycling. 

 
