Oppenheimer & Co. Inc. Raises Stake in Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. (BUFF)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments 

Oppenheimer & Co. Inc. increased its stake in shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:BUFF) by 17.9% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor owned 20,518 shares of the company’s stock after buying an additional 3,122 shares during the period. Oppenheimer & Co. Inc.’s holdings in Blue Buffalo Pet Products were worth $472,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
A number of other large investors also recently bought and sold shares of BUFF. Massachusetts Financial Services Co. MA increased its stake in Blue Buffalo Pet Products by 139.0% in the first quarter. Massachusetts Financial Services Co. MA now owns 2,066,507 shares of the company’s stock valued at $47,530,000 after buying an additional 1,202,040 shares during the period. Mackenzie Financial Corp bought a new stake in Blue Buffalo Pet Products during the first quarter valued at $24,304,000. Renaissance Technologies LLC increased its stake in Blue Buffalo Pet Products by 88.5% in the first quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 2,226,700 shares of the company’s stock valued at $51,214,000 after buying an additional 1,045,700 shares during the period. Norges Bank bought a new stake in Blue Buffalo Pet Products during the fourth quarter valued at $23,156,000. Finally, Wells Fargo & Company MN increased its stake in Blue Buffalo Pet Products by 59.7% in the first quarter. Wells Fargo & Company MN now owns 1,414,921 shares of the company’s stock valued at $32,543,000 after buying an additional 528,903 shares during the period. 88.38% of the stock is owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


