Shares of Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. (BUFF) opened at 22.95 on Wednesday. The firm has a 50-day moving average of $23.23 and a 200-day moving average of $23.99. Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. has a 12 month low of $21.60 and a 12 month high of $27.50. The company has a market capitalization of $4.52 billion, a P/E ratio of 33.75 and a beta of 1.97. 




Blue Buffalo Pet Products (NASDAQ:BUFF) last released its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 9th. The company reported $0.23 earnings per share for the quarter, beating analysts’ consensus estimates of $0.22 by $0.01. The business had revenue of $302 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $300.27 million. Blue Buffalo Pet Products had a net margin of 11.69% and a return on equity of 122.62%. Blue Buffalo Pet Products’s revenue was up 7.9% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period last year, the business earned $0.19 EPS. On average, equities analysts predict that Blue Buffalo Pet Products, Inc. will post $0.92 earnings per share for the current year. 
